SELECTOR="F"
SUMMARIZER="G">    

An Exxon oil tanker ran aground on a reef Friday about 25 miles from
the city of Valdez spilling about 8.4 million gallons of crude oil
into Alaska's Prince William Sound at a reported rate of 10,000
barrels per hour.  There were no reports of injuries to people aboard
the ship or to wildlife.  Local residents and environmentalists
complained about the slow pace of the cleanup, noting that the slick
was huge, looked devastating, and would affect everything in the food
chain.  The spill is expected too add fuel to a campaign by
environmentalists to prevent further oil development in Alaska.</SUM>

<SUM
