Chronology highlights of Exxon Valdez oil spill: March 24, 1989: Exxon
Valdez tankers runs aground on reef south of Valdez, Alaska spilling
nearly 11 million gallons of oil into Prince William Sound; September
15, 1989: Exxon suspends its beach cleanup for winter.  Alaska
officials disagree it was a job well done; November 8, 1989: US House
of Representatives passes bill preserving states' ability to adopt
stricter oil spill liability laws than federal government; February
27, 1990: A federal grand jury indicts Exxon on five criminal
accounts; March 22, 1990: Jury finds Valdez skipper guilty of
negligent discharge of oil but innocent of more serious charges.</SUM>
